  Step 2 (Locate): Name the RE2 parser or automaton component that hosts
    that branch (e.g. `Parser::ParsePerlFlags`, `DFA::RunStateOnByte`,
    `Prog::Compile`, `Regexp::Simplify`).
  Step 3 (Construct): Describe the specific regex feature or token that
    drives the branch (e.g. `(?P<name>...)` Perl named-capture syntax,
    `\p{Greek}` Unicode property, counted repetition `{1000,}`).
  Step 4 (Regex): Emit the final regex string in the `inputs[0].content`
